metadata.name: Distant Views #37
metadata.description:
This work explores generative way of painting landscapes on canvas. Algorithm uses backward moves with big polygon brush to produce mountain-like structures. Shades of randomly selected color make illusion of distance and adds to diversity of terrain. Sun and Moon can have different positions on the horizon or not be visible at all. Their color changes depending on the position. Besides night and day, there are three rough variants of composition based on percentage that sky takes on canvas. There is a also chance to have snowy mountain on top.

Artwork was created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods

December, 2021.

metadata.name: Beam #237
metadata.description:
Warning: GPU intensive!

Editions tiers:
- 125 free
- 125 1tz
- 125 2tz
- 125 3tz
(each tier will be unlocked upon the previous one's completion)

Realistic simulation of an emissive beam traversing a piece of glass of different color and density placed on a metallic surface

(the preview has a resolution factor of 0.75 so it's a bit blurry, the generator has a default of 0.9)

hold the left mouse button and drag to rotate the view around the center

hover with your mouse to spawn some settings controls:
- Resolution (performance-heavy)
- Light bounces
- Frame Samples
- Screenshot Button (takes a screenshot...if it doesn't download, you should open the generator in a new tab)
- Rendering toggle (once you are satisfied with the output you can pause the rendering)

Created with threejs + three-gpu-pathtracer
